          "type": "explanation",
          "name": "Motion blur parameters:",
          "definition": "max blur:............  max amount to blur, as a percentage of the screen\nblur scale:..........  scales blur for a given velocity\ncenter falloff:....... reduces motion blur around the screen center (larger values give smaller reduction regions...)\nexpected dt:.......... expected time per tick, in seconds (used to correct motion blur in fast/slow frames)\n"
        },
        {
          "type": "real",
          "name": "max blur{max blur x}:[0 - 0.2]#max amount to blur, as a percentage of the screen"
        },
        {
          "type": "real",
          "name": "blur scale{blur scale x}:[0 - 0.5]#scales blur for a given velocity"
        },
        {
          "type": "real",
          "name": "center falloff x:[0 - 20]#larger values make smaller areas of no blur"
        },
        {
          "type": "real",
          "name": "center falloff y:[0 - 20]#larger values make smaller areas of no blur"
        },
        {
          "type": "real",
          "name": "expected dt:0.3333 for 30 fps#this is not currently used, but may be in the future"
        },
